#Basic Trees

library(tidyverse)
library(ggtree)
tree <- read.tree("data/tree_newick.nwk")
tree
## 
## Phylogenetic tree with 13 tips and 12 internal nodes.
## 
## Tip labels:
##   A, B, C, D, E, F, ...
## 
## Rooted; includes branch lengths.
ggplot(tree) + geom_tree() + theme_tree()

ggtree(tree)

ggtree(tree) + geom_treescale()

ggtree(tree) + theme_tree2()

ggtree(tree, branch.length = "none")

ggtree(tree, branch.length = "none", color = "blue", size = 2, linetype = 3)

#Exercise 1

1: slanted phylogenetic tree

ggtree(tree, layout = "slanted")

2: circular phylogenetic tree

ggtree(tree, layout= "circular")

3

ggtree(tree, color = "red", size = 3)

#Other tree geoms

p <- ggtree(tree)
p + geom_nodepoint()

p + geom_tippoint()

p + geom_tiplab()

#Exercise 2

ggtree(tree) +
  geom_nodepoint(alpha = 0.5, color = "orange", size = 3) +
  geom_tippoint(color = "purple", shape = "diamond") +
  geom_tiplab(color = "purple") +
  ggtitle("Phylogenetic tree with new aesthetics")

#Internal node number

ggtree(tree) + geom_text(aes(label = node), hjust = -.3)

ggtree(tree) + geom_tiplab()

MRCA(tree, c("C", "E"))
## [1] 17
MRCA(tree, c("G", "H"))
## [1] 21

#Labeling clades

ggtree(tree) +
  geom_cladelabel(node = 17, label = "Some randome clade", color = "red")

ggtree(tree) +
  geom_tiplab() +
  geom_cladelabel(node = 17, label = "Some random clade",
                  color = "red2", offset = .8)

ggtree(tree) + 
  geom_tiplab() +
  geom_cladelabel(node = 17, label = "Some random clade",
                  color = "red2", offset = .8) +
  geom_cladelabel(node = 21, label = "A different clade",
                  color = "blue", offset = .8)

ggtree(tree) + 
  geom_tiplab() + 
  geom_cladelabel(node=17, label="Some random clade", 
                  color="red2", offset=.8, align=TRUE) + 
  geom_cladelabel(node=21, label="A different clade", 
                  color="blue", offset=.8, align=TRUE) + 
  theme_tree2() + 
  xlim(0, 70) + 
  theme_tree()

ggtree(tree) + 
  geom_tiplab() + 
  geom_hilight(node=17, fill="gold") + 
  geom_hilight(node=21, fill="purple")

#Connecting taxa

ggtree(tree) +
  geom_tiplab() +
  geom_taxalink("E", "H", color = "blue") +
  geom_taxalink("C", "G", color  = "orange2", curvature = -.9)

#Exercise 3

ggtree(tree) +
  geom_tiplab() +
  geom_cladelabel(node = 19, label = "Superclade 17", color = "red2", offset = .8, align = TRUE) +
   geom_hilight(node = 19, fill = "blue3") +
  geom_hilight(node = 21, fill = "orange2") +
  geom_taxalink("C", "E", curvature = .3, linetype = 2) +
  geom_taxalink("G", "J", curvature = .4, linetype = 2) +
  theme_tree2() +
  ggtitle("Tree for Exercise 3")

newtree <- read.tree("TOL_fastree_result.tre")
newtree
## 
## Phylogenetic tree with 21 tips and 19 internal nodes.
## 
## Tip labels:
##   Nanoarchaeum_equitans, Pyrococcus_abyssi, Methanocaldococcus_jannaschii, Thermoplasma_volcanium, Halalkalicoccus_jeotgali, Archaeoglobus_fulgidus, ...
## Node labels:
##   , 0.995, 0.952, 0.999, 0.839, 1.000, ...
## 
## Unrooted; includes branch lengths.
ggtree(newtree) +
  geom_text(aes(label = node), hjust = -.3) 

ggtree(newtree, layout = "circular") +
  geom_tiplab() +
  geom_hilight(node = 34, fill = "gold") +
  geom_hilight(node = 29, fill = "blue3") +
  geom_hilight(node = 22, fill = "purple", extend = -.8)
